Value.value: Feck, I'm not goin' in there! I heard weird noises and called the guard!

value.0:
His polished armor glitters in the sun, and the sword held within his hand shines brightly.

This is a rank-and-file soldier of the Southport Guard, dedicated to keeping the peace within the border of the city.

Value.value: *He doesn't look at all happy about being assigned to the sewers.*

value.0: Fashioned from rough iron, these bars extend into a narrow slot in the floor.
Various gears control the locking mechanism of this metal-clad door.

Next to the locked gate, a simple message is etched into a stone placard:

Authorized Personnel Only.
This ladder leads up to a sewer grate.

The air is humid and fetid down here, ripe with the stench of offal, brine, and other unpleasant smells. The ground below the platform under a couple fingers of bay water - and  up to several feet at high tide - that flows slowly northwestward. Nearly everything is coated in some kind of moisture or slime, and the only light is that which filters down from the grates in the street far above, or from the few guttering torches provided.
